The paper focuses on visual saliency models and personalized attention patterns, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG). Finally, the mention of image contents and personal preferences may indicate a connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
